{
  "texts": [
    "The results of the review lead to three main conclusions.",
    "Firstly, most of the simulation models are at the specific level, which limits their reusability.",
    "Secondly, existing generalizable models are not used to build specific models.",
    "Thirdly, most of the models lack a connection between the cyber and the physical world.",
    "Also, the main type of connection used by the models is unidirectional (i.e., digital shadow, a single connection from the physical to the cyber world)."
  ]
}